cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with graph separators, which are a fundamental concept in computational geometry and graph theory. The paper's focus on planar separators and the use of the circle packing theorem suggest that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The results on separators in intersection graphs and nearest neighbor graphs suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely sub-categories. The use of size bounds and complexity analysis suggest that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
